Eren Türkoglu

I'm 21 years old, originally from Türkiye, born in France, and I've spent most of my life between Nancy and Afyon.

Previously, I was the first Software Engineer at Kolizeo where I built the initial web version as an intern. It was used by major sports clubs and reached audiences of up to 3,000 spectators.

In my free time, I build open-source projects such as Chalk, Karp or Sqlite. I also have a blog where I write about stuff I find interesting enough to share.

If anything here piques your interest, don't hesitate to reach out. I love meeting new people!
